text: Saxmundham is a town and civil parish in Suffolk Coastal, Suffolk, England. In 2001, there were 2712 people living in Saxmundham.In 2011 the population was estimated by Suffolk County Council to be 3760. Schools There are two schools in Saxmundham: Saxmundham Primary School and Saxmundham Free School. == References == Category:Suffolk Coastal Category:Civil parishes in Suffolk Category:Towns in Suffolk
